[Term]
id: elmo:3620038
name: nest site creation process
def: "A mechanical ecosystem management process in which a human creates or installs structures to provide nesting, roosting, or denning sites for fauna. Examples include bird nest boxes, raptor nesting platforms, bat boxes, and nesting mounds for turtles." [doi:10.1186/S41610-021-00192-Z]
is_a: elmo:3620020 ! mechanical ecosystem management process
