[Term]
id: elmo:3620039
name: perch and roost creation process
def: "A mechanical ecosystem management process in which a human creates structures such as posts, platforms, or dead snags for wildlife to perch or roost on. Such structures are used by birds of prey, bats, and other arboreal fauna." [doi:10.1007/s11258-016-0619-4]
is_a: elmo:3620020 ! mechanical ecosystem management process
