[Term]
id: elmo:3620041
name: riparian buffer strip creation process
def: "A mechanical ecosystem management process in which a human establishes strips of vegetation in the riparian areas of watercourses such as rivers, streams, and creeks." [doi:10.1890/08-2064.1]
is_a: elmo:3620040 ! buffer strip creation process
