[Term]
id: elmo:3620042
name: buffer strip retention process
def: "A mechanical ecosystem management process in which a human leaves strips of vegetation untouched when clearing land for other purposes, with the goal of retaining their ecological function as a buffer between landscape features." [doi:10.2134/jeq2018.03.0120]
