[Term]
id: elmo:3620054
name: shoreline reinforcement process
def: "An earthworks process in which a human installs material, which may be inorganic (e.g. rock riprap, geotextile mesh) or organic (e.g. timber cribbing, live stakes), to stabilize the bank of a body of water and reduce erosion." [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cellular_confinement]
