[Term]
id: elmo:3620057
name: natural channel realignment process
def: "An earthworks process in which a human realigns the channel of a stream by digging out replacement pathways and filling existing ones with the goal of recreating a natural pool-riffle-pool meander sequence." [https://streamhandbook.org/project/stream-channel-realignment/]
