[Term]
id: elmo:3620060
name: topsoil removal process
def: "A mechanical ecosystem management process in which a human removes the topsoil layer (the upper soil horizon rich in organic matter and nutrients) from an area, either to reduce excess nutrients that favour invasive species or to harvest donor soil containing seeds and soil biota for use elsewhere." [doi:10.1111/avsc.12063]
