property_value: IAO:0000116 "Exact synonym with eIVC biome." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620214
name: Anthropogenic subterranean voids biome
def: "The anthropogenic subterranean voids biome is a biome that  includes a single functional group of ecosystems that owe their genesis to excavation by humans. They include underground mines, transport tunnels, tombs, defence and energy installations, and other infrastructure." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/S2]
synonym: "S2 Anthropogenic subterranean voids biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620215
name: Subterranean freshwaters biome
def: "The subterranean freshwaters biome is a biome that includes streams, small lakes and aquifers beneath the earth’s surface and potentially has the largest volume of water of all the freshwater biomes." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/SF1]
synonym: "SF1 Subterranean freshwaters biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620216
name: Anthropogenic subterranean freshwaters biome
def: "The anthropogenic subterranean freshwaters biome is a biome that includes aquatic systems in underground canals, drains, sewers, water pipes, and flooded mines constructed by humans. These are usually well connected to surface waters." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/SF2]
synonym: "SF2 Anthropogenic subterranean freshwaters biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620217
name: Palustrine wetlands biome
def: "The palustrine wetlands biome is a biome that includes vegetated floodplains, groundwater seeps, and mires with permanent or intermittent surface water. Although water and light are abundant at least periodically, saturation of the soil may result in oxygen deprivation below the ground. This suppresses microbial activity and, in many systems, production exceeds decomposition, resulting in peat accumulation." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/TF1]
synonym: "Palustrine Wetland" EXACT []
synonym: "TF1" EXACT []
synonym: "TF1 Palustrine wetlands biome" EXACT []
synonym: "TP1" EXACT []
synonym: "TP1 Palustrine Wetland" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Exact synonym with eIVC biome." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620218
name: Rivers and streams biome
def: "The rivers and streams biome is a biome that includes lotic (running water) ecosystems, flowing from elevated uplands or underground springs to deltas, estuaries, and lakes. They are defined primarily by their linear structure, unidirectional flow regimes, and close interaction with the surrounding landscape." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/F1]
synonym: "F1 Rivers and streams biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620219
name: Lakes biome
def: "The lakes biome is a biome that includes lentic ecosystems defined by their still waters. They vary in area, depth, water regime, and connectivity to other aquatic systems across a global distribution." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/F2]
synonym: "F2 Lakes biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620220
name: Artificial wetlands biome
def: "The artificial wetlands biome is a biome that includes built structures that hold or transfer water for human use, treatment, or disposal, including large storage reservoirs, farm dams or ponds, recreational and ornamental wetlands, rice paddies, freshwater aquafarms, wastewater storages and treatment ponds, and canals, ditches and drains." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/F3]
synonym: "F3 Artificial wetlands biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620221
name: Semi-confined transitional waters biome
def: "The semi-confined transitional waters biome is a biome that includes coastal inlets that are influenced by inputs of both fresh and marine water from terrestrial catchments and ocean tides, waves, and currents. They include deep-water coastal inlets or fjords mostly restricted to high latitudes, as well as estuaries, bays, and lagoons, which are scattered around coastlines throughout the world." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/FM1]
synonym: "FM1 Semi-confined transitional waters biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620222
name: Marine shelf biome
def: "The marine shelf biome is a biome that is distributed globally between the shoreline and deep sea-floor biomes and is dominated by benthic productivity. It includes ecosystems with biogenic substrates (such as seagrass meadows, kelp forests, oyster beds, and coral reefs) and minerogenic substrates including rocky reefs, sandy bottoms, and muddy bottoms." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/M1]
synonym: "M1 Marine shelf biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620223
name: Pelagic ocean waters biome
def: "The pelagic ocean waters biome is a biome that comprises the open-ocean water column across all latitudes." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/M2]
synonym: "M2 Pelagic ocean waters biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from Ecosystem Properties section of IUCN - needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620224
name: Deep sea floors biome
def: "The deep sea floors biome is a biome that includes the entire oceanic benthos below ~250 m depth, where there is not enough light to support primary productivity through photosynthesis. It extends from the upper bathyal seafloor to the deepest parts of the ocean, at just under 11 km in the Mariana Trench." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/M3]
synonym: "M3 Deep sea floors biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620225
name: Anthropogenic marine biome
def: "The anthropogenic marine biome is a biome that includes constructed, deposited or dumped artificial structures in the oceans that either confine managed marine organisms or attract marine biota that would not otherwise occupy such locations." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/M4]
synonym: "M4 Anthropogenic marine biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620226
name: Shorelines biome
def: "The shorelines biome is a biome that includes naturally formed, intertidal abiogenic habitats situated at the interface between land and sea. The distribution of the biome spans all latitudes (temperate to polar) at which landmasses are present." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/MT1]
synonym: "Marine Shoreline" EXACT []
synonym: "MS1 Marine Shoreline" EXACT []
synonym: "MT1" EXACT []
synonym: "MT1 Shorelines biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Exact synonym with eIVC biome." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620227
name: Supralittoral coast biome
def: "The supralittoral coastal biome includes the landward extent of the transition from marine to terrestrial biomes. It is elevated above the direct influence of waves and tides (see the Shoreline biome) and beyond the direct influence of freshwater seepage or rivers (see brackish tidal biota). Supratidal coastal ecosystems extend around all the world’s land masses, occupying a fringe from tens of metres to a few kilometres wide and covering the entire extent of many small islands." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/MT2]
synonym: "MS2" EXACT []
synonym: "MS2 Supralittoral Marine Coast" EXACT []
synonym: "MT2" EXACT []
synonym: "MT2 Supralittoral coast biome" EXACT []
synonym: "Supralittoral Marine Coast" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Exact synonym with eIVC biome." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620228
name: Anthropogenic shorelines biome
def: "The anthropogenic shorelines biome is a biome that is distributed globally where urbanised and industrial areas adjoin the coast, and includes some more remote structures such as artificial islands. It includes marine interfaces constructed from hard, smooth surfaces, including concrete, timber, lithic blocks, and earthen fill, adjoining, extending or replacing natural shores, or floating in proximity to them." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/MT3]
synonym: "Anthropogenic Marine Shoreline" EXACT []
synonym: "MS3" EXACT []
synonym: "MS3 Anthropogenic Marine Shoreline" EXACT []
synonym: "MT3" EXACT []
synonym: "MT3 Anthropogenic shorelines biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Exact synonym with eIVC biome." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620229
name: Brackish tidal biome
def: "The brackish tidal biome is a biome that is associated with prograding depositional shorelines at the interface of terrestrial, freshwater, and marine realms. The relative influences of marine, freshwater, and terrestrial processes vary from strongly fluvial deltas to marine-dominated intertidal forests and terrestrial-dominated coastal saltmarsh." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/MFT1]
synonym: "Brackish Tidal Wetland" EXACT []
synonym: "MB1" EXACT []
synonym: "MB1 Brackish Tidal Wetland" EXACT []
synonym: "MFT1" EXACT []
synonym: "MFT1 Brackish tidal biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from IUCN GET. Needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620230
name: Tropical alpine grasslands and herbfields
def: "Treeless mountain systems dominated by an open to dense cover of cold-tolerant C3 perennial tussock grasses, herbs, small shrubs, and distinctive arborescent rosette or cushion growth forms. Lichens and bryophytes are also common. Productivity is low, dependent on autochthonous energy, and limited by cold temperatures, diurnal freeze-thaw cycles, and desiccating conditions, but not by a short growing season (as in T6.4). Elfin forms of tropical montane forests (T1.3) occupy sheltered gullies and lower elevations. Diversity is low to moderate but endemism is high among some taxa, reflecting steep elevational gradients, microhabitat heterogeneity, and topographic insularity, which restricts dispersal. Solifluction (i.e. the slow flow of saturated soil downslope) restricts seedling establishment to stable microsites. Plants have traits to protect buds, leaves, and reproductive tissues from diurnal cold and transient desiccation stress, including ramulose (i.e. many-branched), cushion, and rosette growth forms, insulation from marcescent (i.e. dead) leaves or pectin fluids, diminutive leaf sizes, leaf pubescence, water storage in stem-pith, and vegetative propagation. Most plants are long-lived and some rosette forms are semelparous. Cuticle and epidermal layers reduce UV-B transmission to photosynthetic tissues. Plant coexistence is mediated by competition, facilitation, herbivory (vertebrate and invertebrate), and fire regimes. Simple trophic networks include itinerant large herbivores and predators from adjacent lowland savannas as well as resident reptiles, small mammals, and macro-invertebrates." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/groups/T6.5]
synonym: "T6.5" EXACT []
synonym: "T6.5 Tropical alpine grasslands and shrublands" EXACT []
synonym: "Tropical High Montane Grassland & Herbfield" EXACT []
synonym: "TT6.c1" EXACT []
synonym: "TT6.c1 Tropical High Montane Grassland & Herbfield" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620212 ! Polar/alpine (cryogenic) biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from Ecosystem Properties section of IUCN - needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620231
name: Annual croplands
def: "High-productivity croplands are maintained by the intensive anthropogenic supplementation of nutrients, water, and artificial disturbance regimes (e.g. annual cultivation), translocation (e.g. sowing), and harvesting of annual plants. These systems are typically dominated by one or few shallow-rooted short-lived plant species such as grains (mostly C3 grasses), vegetables, �flowers�, legumes, or fibre species harvested annually by humans for the commercial or subsistence production of food, materials, or ornamental displays. Disequilibrium community structure and composition is maintained by translocations and/or managed reproduction of target species and usually by periodic application of herbicides and pesticides and/or culling to exclude competitors, predators, herbivores, and/or pathogens. Consequently, compared to antecedent �natural� systems, croplands are structurally simple, have low functional, genetic, and taxonomic diversity and no local endemism. Subsistence croplands, including Swidden rotation systems, are typically more diverse than industrial croplands. Productivity is highly sensitive to variations in resource availability. Target biota are genetically manipulated by selective breeding or molecular engineering to promote rapid growth rates, efficient resource capture, enhanced resource allocation to production tissues, and tolerance to harsh environmental conditions, insect predators, and diseases. Typically, at least 40% of net primary productivity is appropriated by humans. Croplands may be rotated inter-annually with livestock pastures or fallow fields (T7.2) or may be integrated into mixed cropping-livestock systems. Target biota coexists with a cosmopolitan ruderal biota (e.g. weedy plants, mice, and starlings) that exploits production landscapes opportunistically through efficient dispersal, itinerant foraging, rapid establishment, high fecundity, and rapid population turnover. Native biota from adjoining non-anthropogenic systems may also interact with croplands. When actively managed systems are abandoned or managed less intensively, these non-target biota, especially non-woody plants, become dominant and may form a steady, self-maintaining state or a transitional phase to novel ecosystems." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/groups/T7.1]
synonym: "Annual Cropland" EXACT []
synonym: "T7.1" EXACT []
synonym: "T7.1 Annual croplands" EXACT []
synonym: "TT7.a1" EXACT []
synonym: "TT7.a1 Annual Cropland" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620213 ! Intensive land-use biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from Ecosystem Properties section of IUCN - needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620232
name: Constructed lacustrine wetlands
def: "Shallow, open water bodies have been constructed in diverse landscapes and climates. They may be fringed by amphibious vegetation, or else bedrock or bare soil maintained by earthworks or livestock trampling. Emergents rarely extend throughout the water body, but submerged macrophytes are often present. Productivity ranges from very high in wastewater ponds to low in mining and excavation pits, depending on depth, shape, history and management. Taxonomic and functional diversity range from levels comparable to natural lakes to much less, depending on productivity, complexity of aquatic or fringing vegetation, water quality, management and proximity to other waterbodies or vegetation. Trophic structure includes phytoplankton and microbial detritivores, with planktonic and invertebrate predators dominating limnetic zones. Macrophytes may occur in shallow littoral zones or submerged habitats, and some artificial water bodies include higher trophic levels including macroinvertebrates, amphibians, turtles, fish, and waterbirds. Fish may be introduced by people or arrive by flows connected to source populations, where these exist. Endemism is generally low, but these waterbodies may be important refuges for some species now highly depleted in their natural habitats. Life histories often reflect those found in natural waterbodies nearby, but widely dispersed opportunists dominate where water quality is poor. Intermittent water bodies support biota with drought resistance or avoidance traits, while permanently inundated systems provide habitat for mobile species such as waterbirds." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/groups/F3.2]
synonym: "F3.2 Constructed lacustrine wetlands" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620220 ! Artificial wetlands biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from Ecosystem Properties section of IUCN - needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620233
name: Marine aquafarms
def: "Marine aquafarms (i.e. mariculture) are localised, high-productivity systems within and around enclosures constructed for the breeding, rearing, and harvesting of marine plants and animals, including finfish, molluscs, crustaceans, algae, and other marine plants. Allochthonous energy and nutrient inputs are delivered by humans and by diffusion from surrounding marine waters. Autochthonous inputs are small and produced by pelagic algae or biofilms on the infrastructure, unless the target species are aquatic macrophytes. More commonly, target species are consumers that belong to middle or upper trophic levels. Diversity is low across taxa, and the trophic web is dominated by a super-abundance of target species. Where multiple target species are cultivated, they are selected to ensure neutral or mutualistic interactions with one another (e.g. detritivores that consume the waste of a higher-level consumer). Target biota are harvested periodically to produce food, fish meal, nutrient agar, horticultural products, jewellery, and cosmetics. Their high population densities are maintained by continual inputs of food and regular re-stocking to compensate harvest. Target species may be genetically modified and are often bred in intensive hatcheries and then released into the enclosures. Food and nutrient inputs may promote the abundance of non-target species including opportunistic microalgae, zooplankton, and pathogens and predators of the target species. These pest species or their impacts may be controlled by antibiotics or herbicides or by culling (e.g. pinnipeds around fish farms). The enclosures constitute barriers to the movement of larger organisms, but some cultivated stock may escape, while wild individuals from the surrounding waters may invade the enclosure. Enclosures are generally permeable to small organisms, propagules and waste products of larger organisms, nutrients, and pathogens, enabling the ecosystem to extend beyond the confines of the infrastructure." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/groups/M4.2]
synonym: "M4.2 Marine aquafarms" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620225 ! Anthropogenic marine biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition taken from Ecosystem Properties section of IUCN - needs to be reformatted for ontology." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620234
name: Subterranean lithic biome
def: "The subterranean lithic biome is a biome that includes non-aquatic lithic systems beneath the earth’s surface where sunlight is absent or of insufficient intensity to sustain photosynthesis." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/biomes/S1]
synonym: "S1 Subterranean lithic biome" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem

[Term]
id: elmo:3620235
name: biome
def: "An ecosystem delineated by broad features of structure and common major ecological drivers, typically global in scale." [https://global-ecosystems.org/page/typology]
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem

[Term]
id: elmo:3620236
name: Tropical Savanna & Shrubland Biome
def: "A biome which contains tropical savannas and shrublands." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298929/Tropical_Savanna_Shrubland_Biome]
synonym: "TT3 Tropical Savanna & Shrubland" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition still being developed by eIVC team." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620237
name: Temperate-Boreal Grassland & Shrubland Biome
def: "A biome which contains grasslands and shrublands and is located in the temperate-boreal climactic region." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298930/Temperate-Boreal_Grassland_Shrubland_Biome]
synonym: "TT4 Temperate-Boreal Grassland & Shrubland" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition still being developed by eIVC team." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620238
name: Freshwater Coast Biome
def: "A biome which occurs at the coast of a freshwater body of water." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298935/Freshwater_Coast_Biome]
synonym: "TP2 Freshwater Coast" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition still being developed by eIVC team." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620239
name: Anthropogenic Freshwater Coast Biome
def: "A biome which occurs at the coast of an anthropogenic body of water." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298936/Anthropogenic_Freshwater_Coast_Biome]
synonym: "TP3 Anthropogenic Freshwater Coast" EXACT []
is_a: ENVO:01001110 ! ecosystem
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition still being developed by eIVC team." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620240
name: Tropical Rainforest Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Tropical-subtropical forests biome comprising closed-canopy, high-rainfall tropical and subtropical forests characterised by high biodiversity, year-round productivity, and complex multi-layered canopy structure." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298942/Tropical_Rainforest_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT1.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TT1.a Tropical Rainforest Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620207 ! Tropical-subtropical forests biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620241
name: Tropical Dry Forest Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Tropical-subtropical forests biome comprising seasonally dry tropical and subtropical forests and thickets characterised by drought-deciduous or semi-deciduous phenology and strongly seasonal productivity." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298943/Tropical_Dry_Forest_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT1.b" EXACT []
synonym: "TT1.b Tropical Dry Forest Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620207 ! Tropical-subtropical forests biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620242
name: Warm Temperate Forest & Woodland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Temperate-boreal forests and woodlands biome comprising warm temperate forests and woodlands characterised by mixed evergreen-deciduous or evergreen canopies with moderate biodiversity and mild seasonal climates." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298945/Warm_Temperate_Forest_Woodland_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT2.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TT2.a Warm Temperate Forest & Woodland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620208 ! Temperate-boreal forests and woodlands biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620243
name: Cool Temperate Forest & Woodland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Temperate-boreal forests and woodlands biome comprising cool temperate forests and woodlands characterised by deciduous or mixed canopies, pronounced seasonality, and moderate to high productivity." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1333041/Cool_Temperate_Forest_Woodland_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT2.b" EXACT []
synonym: "TT2.b Cool Temperate Forest & Woodland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620208 ! Temperate-boreal forests and woodlands biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620244
name: Boreal Forest & Woodland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Temperate-boreal forests and woodlands biome comprising boreal forests and woodlands at high latitudes characterised by coniferous or mixed canopies, cold long winters, and a short growing season." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298944/Boreal_Forest_Woodland_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT2.c" EXACT []
synonym: "TT2.c Boreal Forest & Woodland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620208 ! Temperate-boreal forests and woodlands biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620245
name: Tropical Savanna Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Tropical Savanna and Shrubland biome comprising open to semi-closed tropical savannas characterised by a continuous grass layer, scattered trees, and strongly seasonal rainfall with a pronounced dry season." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298946/Tropical_Savanna_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT3.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TT3.a Tropical Savanna Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620236 ! Tropical Savanna & Shrubland Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620246
name: Tropical Shrubland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Tropical Savanna and Shrubland biome comprising tropical shrublands characterised by woody shrub dominance, often on nutrient-poor or seasonally dry substrates with recurrent disturbance by fire or herbivory." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298947/Tropical_Shrubland_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT3.b" EXACT []
synonym: "TT3.b Tropical Shrubland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620236 ! Tropical Savanna & Shrubland Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620247
name: Tropical Open Rock Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Tropical Savanna and Shrubland biome comprising tropical cliff and rock outcrop ecosystems characterised by exposed rock substrates, extreme microclimate variability, sparse vegetation, and high local endemism." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298948/Tropical_Open_Rock_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT3.c" EXACT []
synonym: "TT3.c Tropical Open Rock Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620236 ! Tropical Savanna & Shrubland Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620248
name: Mediterranean-Dry Grassland & Shrubland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Temperate-Boreal Grassland and Shrubland biome comprising Mediterranean-climate and dry temperate grasslands and shrublands characterised by fire-adapted or drought-adapted vegetation and pronounced summer drought." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1333042/Mediterranean-Dry_Grassland_Shrubland_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT4.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TT4.a Mediterranean-Dry Grassland & Shrubland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620237 ! Temperate-Boreal Grassland & Shrubland Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620249
name: Temperate Grassland & Shrubland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Temperate-Boreal Grassland and Shrubland biome comprising temperate grasslands and shrublands characterised by a dominant grass and forb layer with limited woody cover and seasonal moisture deficits." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298949/Temperate_Grassland_Shrubland_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT4.b" EXACT []
synonym: "TT4.b Temperate Grassland & Shrubland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620237 ! Temperate-Boreal Grassland & Shrubland Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620250
name: Continental Boreal Shrubland & Grassland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Temperate-Boreal Grassland and Shrubland biome comprising continental boreal shrublands and grasslands at high latitudes characterised by cold continental climates, short growing seasons, and low productivity." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298950/Continental_Boreal_Shrubland_Grassland_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT4.c" EXACT []
synonym: "TT4.c Continental Boreal Shrubland & Grassland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620237 ! Temperate-Boreal Grassland & Shrubland Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620251
name: Temperate-Boreal Open Rock Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Temperate-Boreal Grassland and Shrubland biome comprising temperate and boreal cliff and rock outcrop ecosystems characterised by minimal soil development, stress-tolerant vegetation, and high local endemism." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298951/Temperate-Boreal_Open_Rock_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT4.d" EXACT []
synonym: "TT4.d Temperate-Boreal Open Rock Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620237 ! Temperate-Boreal Grassland & Shrubland Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620252
name: Cool Semi-desert Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Deserts and semi-deserts biome comprising cool arid and semi-arid ecosystems characterised by low and variable precipitation, cold winters, and sparse shrub-steppe or herbaceous vegetation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298952/Cool_Semi-desert_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT5.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TT5.a Cool Semi-desert Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620211 ! Deserts and semi-deserts biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620253
name: Warm Desert & Semi-desert Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Deserts and semi-deserts biome comprising warm arid and hyper-arid ecosystems characterised by extreme heat, very low precipitation, and highly drought-adapted sparse vegetation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298953/Warm_Desert_Semi-desert_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT5.b" EXACT []
synonym: "TT5.b Warm Desert & Semi-desert Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620211 ! Deserts and semi-deserts biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620254
name: Polar & Alpine Snow & Ice Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Polar/alpine (cryogenic) biome comprising polar and high-altitude snow and ice ecosystems characterised by perennial or semi-permanent ice or snow cover and minimal biological productivity." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298954/Polar_Alpine_Snow_Ice_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT6.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TT6.a Polar & Alpine Snow & Ice Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620212 ! Polar/alpine (cryogenic) biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620255
name: Temperate-Polar Alpine & Tundra Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Polar/alpine (cryogenic) biome comprising temperate to polar alpine and tundra ecosystems characterised by cold temperatures, short growing seasons, permafrost or freeze-thaw cycles, and low-growing vegetation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298955/Temperate-Polar_Alpine_Tundra_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT6.b" EXACT []
synonym: "TT6.b Temperate-Polar Alpine & Tundra Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620212 ! Polar/alpine (cryogenic) biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620256
name: Tropical Alpine Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Polar/alpine (cryogenic) biome comprising high-altitude tropical alpine ecosystems characterised by intense UV radiation, large diurnal temperature variation, and distinctive Afroalpine or Andean vegetation forms." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298956/Tropical_Alpine_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT6.c" EXACT []
synonym: "TT6.c Tropical Alpine Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620212 ! Polar/alpine (cryogenic) biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620257
name: Agricultural Land Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Intensive land-use biome comprising cultivated croplands, pastures, and managed farmlands characterised by human modification of the land surface for food, fibre, and biomass production." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298957/Agricultural_Land_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT7.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TT7.a Agricultural Land Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620213 ! Intensive land-use biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620258
name: Developed Land Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Intensive land-use biome comprising urban, suburban, and built-up lands characterised by impervious surfaces, human infrastructure, and heavily modified ecological conditions." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298958/Developed_Land_Subbiome]
synonym: "TT7.b" EXACT []
synonym: "TT7.b Developed Land Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620213 ! Intensive land-use biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620259
name: Derived Land Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Intensive land-use biome comprising derived semi-natural lands such as plantation forests and highly modified vegetation characterised by human-altered successional trajectories and managed species composition." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/groups/T7]
synonym: "TT7.c" EXACT []
synonym: "TT7.c Derived Land Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620213 ! Intensive land-use biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "No link on NatureServe Explorer." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620260
name: Forested Wetland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Palustrine wetlands biome comprising freshwater forested wetlands characterised by waterlogged soils supporting tree-dominated canopies adapted to periodic or permanent inundation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298960/Forested_Wetland_Subbiome]
synonym: "TP1.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TP1.a Forested Wetland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620217 ! Palustrine wetlands biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620261
name: Emergent Open Wetland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Palustrine wetlands biome comprising open freshwater wetlands characterised by emergent herbaceous or shrubby vegetation and standing or slow-moving water with seasonal to permanent inundation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298961/Emergent_Open_Wetland_Subbiome]
synonym: "TP1.b" EXACT []
synonym: "TP1.b Emergent Open Wetland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620217 ! Palustrine wetlands biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620262
name: Bog & Fen Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Palustrine wetlands biome comprising peat-forming freshwater wetlands characterised by waterlogged, nutrient-poor, and often acidic conditions supporting sphagnum moss, sedge, and heath communities." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298962/Bog_Fen_Subbiome]
synonym: "TP1.c" EXACT []
synonym: "TP1.c Bog & Fen Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620217 ! Palustrine wetlands biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620263
name: Freshwater Coast Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Freshwater Coast biome comprising natural freshwater shoreline ecosystems characterised by dynamic water-level fluctuations, wave or current action, and characteristic riparian or lacustrine shore vegetation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298964/Freshwater_Coast_Subbiome]
synonym: "TP2.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TP2.a Freshwater Coast Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620238 ! Freshwater Coast Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620264
name: Developed Freshwater Coast Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Anthropogenic Freshwater Coast biome comprising modified and developed freshwater shoreline ecosystems characterised by human infrastructure, altered hydrological regimes, and degraded or managed shoreline vegetation." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/groups/TF1]
synonym: "TP3.a" EXACT []
synonym: "TP3.a Developed Freshwater Coast Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620239 ! Anthropogenic Freshwater Coast Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "No link on NatureServe Explorer." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620265
name: Coastal Brackish Tidal Wetland Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Brackish tidal biome comprising coastal wetlands subject to tidal influence and salinity gradients, characterised by emergent macrophytes such as saltmarsh grasses, mangroves, or halophytic vegetation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298966/Coastal_Brackish_Tidal_Wetland_Subbiome]
synonym: "MB1.a" EXACT []
synonym: "MB1.a Coastal Brackish Tidal Wetland Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620229 ! Brackish tidal biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620266
name: Marine-Intertidal Shoreline Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Shorelines biome comprising natural marine intertidal shoreline ecosystems characterised by regular tidal exposure, wave action, and communities of salt-tolerant organisms adapted to alternating aerial and aquatic conditions." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298967/Marine-Intertidal_Shoreline_Subbiome]
synonym: "MS1.a" EXACT []
synonym: "MS1.a Marine-Intertidal Shoreline Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620226 ! Shorelines biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620267
name: Supralittoral Marine Coast Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Supralittoral coast biome comprising coastal ecosystems above the high tide mark characterised by salt spray, periodic inundation, wind disturbance, and distinctive coastal dune or cliff vegetation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298968/Supralittoral_Marine_Coast_Subbiome]
synonym: "MS2.a" EXACT []
synonym: "MS2.a Supralittoral Marine Coast Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620227 ! Supralittoral coast biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620268
name: Developed Marine Shoreline Subbiome
def: "A subbiome of the Anthropogenic shorelines biome comprising developed and modified marine shoreline ecosystems characterised by human infrastructure such as seawalls, breakwaters, and hardened coastlines." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298969/Developed_Marine_Shoreline_Subbiome]
synonym: "MS3.a" EXACT []
synonym: "MS3.a Developed Marine Shoreline Subbiome" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620228 ! Anthropogenic shorelines biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620269
name: Tropical Thorn Woodland
def: "A tropical dry forest ecosystem characterised by thorny, drought-adapted trees and shrubs with sparse to moderate canopy cover, occurring in semi-arid tropical regions with a prolonged dry season." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298975/Tropical_Thorn_Woodland_Ecobiome]
synonym: "TT1.b2" EXACT []
synonym: "TT1.b2 Tropical Thorn Woodland" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620241 ! Tropical Dry Forest Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620270
name: Temperate Continental Conifer Forest & Woodland
def: "A cool temperate forest and woodland ecosystem characterised by coniferous tree dominance in continental climates, with cold winters, moderate growing-season productivity, and often a sparse or ericaceous understorey." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298982/Temperate_Continental_Conifer_Forest_Woodland_Ecobiome]
synonym: "TT2.b3" EXACT []
synonym: "TT2.b3 Temperate Continental Conifer Forest & Woodland" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620243 ! Cool Temperate Forest & Woodland Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620271
name: Boreal Forest & Woodland
def: "A boreal forest and woodland ecosystem characterised by coniferous tree dominance, a moss- and lichen-dominated understorey, seasonally frozen soils, and a short growing season at high latitudes." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298976/Boreal_Forest_Woodland_Ecobiome]
synonym: "TT2.c1" EXACT []
synonym: "TT2.c1 Boreal Forest & Woodland" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620244 ! Boreal Forest & Woodland Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620272
name: Tropical Lowland Savanna
def: "A tropical savanna ecosystem characterised by a continuous grass layer interspersed with scattered trees or shrubs in lowland tropical regions, maintained by seasonal drought, fire, and herbivory." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298983/Tropical_Lowland_Savanna_Ecobiome]
synonym: "ELMO:3620114" NARROW []
synonym: "ELMO:3620115" NARROW []
synonym: "ELMO:3620116" NARROW []
synonym: "TT3.a1" EXACT []
synonym: "TT3.a1 Tropical Lowland Savanna" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620245 ! Tropical Savanna Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620273
name: Tropical Cliff & Rock Outcrop
def: "A tropical open-rock ecosystem characterised by exposed cliff and rock outcrop substrates, minimal soil, extreme microclimate variability, and highly specialised stress-tolerant plant communities with high local endemism." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298985/Tropical_Cliff_Rock_Outcrop_Ecobiome]
synonym: "ELMO:3620113" BROAD []
synonym: "TT3.c1" EXACT []
synonym: "TT3.c1 Tropical Cliff & Rock Outcrop" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620247 ! Tropical Open Rock Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620274
name: Boreal Shrubland & Grassland
def: "A continental boreal ecosystem characterised by dwarf shrub or grass-dominated vegetation in cold, continental climates, typically occupying areas beyond or above the boreal forest tree line with a short growing season." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298989/Boreal_Shrubland_Grassland_Ecobiome]
synonym: "TT4.c1" EXACT []
synonym: "TT4.c1 Boreal Shrubland & Grassland" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620250 ! Continental Boreal Shrubland & Grassland Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620275
name: Temperate-Boreal Cliff & Rock Outcrop
def: "A temperate to boreal open-rock ecosystem characterised by exposed cliff faces and rock outcrops supporting stress-tolerant vascular plants, lichens, and bryophytes adapted to shallow soils and temperature extremes." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298990/Temperate-Boreal_Cliff_Rock_Outcrop_Ecobiome]
synonym: "ELMO:3620113" BROAD []
synonym: "TT4.d1" EXACT []
synonym: "TT4.d1 Temperate-Boreal Cliff & Rock Outcrop" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620251 ! Temperate-Boreal Open Rock Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620276
name: Cool Desert & Semi-desert Shrub-Steppe
def: "A cool desert and semi-desert ecosystem characterised by a sparse cover of cold-tolerant shrubs and grasses on arid substrates, with low and variable precipitation, cold winters, and biological soil crusts." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298991/Cool_Desert_Semi-desert_Shrub-Steppe_Ecobiome]
synonym: "ELMO:3620119" NARROW []
synonym: "ELMO:3620122" NARROW []
synonym: "TT5.a1" EXACT []
synonym: "TT5.a1 Cool Desert & Semi-desert Shrub-Steppe" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620252 ! Cool Semi-desert Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620277
name: Polar Tundra & Desert
def: "A polar to alpine tundra and desert ecosystem characterised by permafrost, low temperatures, a brief growing season, and low-growing vegetation dominated by grasses, sedges, mosses, lichens, and dwarf shrubs." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298996/Polar_Tundra_Desert_Ecobiome]
is_a: elmo:3620255 ! Temperate-Polar Alpine & Tundra Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620278
name: Temperate Alpine Grassland & Shrubland
def: "A temperate alpine ecosystem characterised by open grasslands and shrublands above the treeline, with short growing seasons, intense UV radiation, freeze-thaw cycles, and wind-adapted low-growing vegetation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1298997/Temperate_Alpine_Grassland_Shrubland_Ecobiome]
synonym: "TT6.b2" EXACT []
synonym: "TT6.b2 Temperate Alpine Grassland & Shrubland" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620255 ! Temperate-Polar Alpine & Tundra Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620279
name: Marsh, Wet Meadow & Shrub Wetland
def: "An emergent open wetland ecosystem characterised by seasonally to permanently waterlogged soils supporting a continuous cover of herbaceous marsh plants, wet meadow grasses and sedges, or low wetland shrubs." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1299006/Marsh_Wet_Meadow_Shrub_Wetland_Ecobiome]
synonym: "TP1.b1" EXACT []
synonym: "TP1.b1 Marsh, Wet Meadow & Shrub Wetland" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620261 ! Emergent Open Wetland Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620280
name: Episodic Arid floodplain
def: "An emergent open wetland ecosystem characterised by irregular and episodic flooding of arid or semi-arid lowlands, supporting ephemeral wetland communities that respond rapidly to infrequent flooding events." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1299007/Episodic_Arid_Floodplain_Ecobiome]
is_a: elmo:3620261 ! Emergent Open Wetland Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620281
name: Inland Salt Marsh
def: "An emergent open wetland ecosystem characterised by saline or brackish soils in inland settings, dominated by halophytic herbaceous vegetation adapted to osmotic stress and periodic inundation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1299008/Inland_Salt_Marsh_Ecobiome]
is_a: elmo:3620261 ! Emergent Open Wetland Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620282
name: Coastal Freshwater Shore & Dune
def: "A freshwater coastal ecosystem characterised by dynamic shoreline substrates of sand, gravel, or organic material along lake or river margins, supporting sparse to dense shoreline and dune vegetation." [https://explorer.natureserve.org/Taxon/ELEMENT_GLOBAL.2.1299012/Coastal_Freshwater_Shore_Dune_Ecobiome]
is_a: elmo:3620238 ! Freshwater Coast Biome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620283
name: Developed Freshwater Shoreline
def: "A developed freshwater coast ecosystem characterised by artificially modified shorelines of lakes, reservoirs, or rivers, including riprap, seawalls, and other engineered structures that alter natural shoreline processes." [https://global-ecosystems.org/explore/groups/TF1]
synonym: "TP3.a1" EXACT []
synonym: "TP3.a1 Developed Freshwater Shoreline" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620264 ! Developed Freshwater Coast Subbiome
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Definition sourced from IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology (https://global-ecosystems.org) and adapted for ontology use." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "No link on NatureServe Explorer." xsd:string

[Term]
id: elmo:3620500
name: chemical ecosystem management process
def: "An active ecosystem management process in which a human applys or releases a chemical substance to realize some ecological management goal." [doi:10.1016/j.scitotenv.2021.148631]
