id: elmo:3621024
name: tile drain installation process
def: "A mechanical hydrological alteration process in which a human installs subsurface tile drains to manage soil water levels, typically to reduce drainage from waterlogged soils or to control water levels on a restoration site." []
is_a: elmo:3620033 ! mechanical hydrological alteration process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621025
name: water control structure installation process
def: "A mechanical hydrological alteration process in which a human installs a water control structure such as a weir, sluice gate, or stop-log to regulate water levels in a wetland, stream, or drainage ditch for ecological restoration purposes." []
synonym: "sluice installation" EXACT []
synonym: "weir installation" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620033 ! mechanical hydrological alteration process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621026
name: fungicide application process
def: "A chemical application process in which a human applies a fungicide to a restoration site or to plant material in order to manage fungal pathogens that threaten plants or other organisms of conservation concern." []
is_a: elmo:3620501 ! chemical application process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.2" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.2
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621027
name: soil acidification process
def: "A chemical application process in which a human applies an acidifying amendment such as elemental sulfur to soil or water in order to lower the pH and improve conditions for acid-tolerant species such as heathland or bog vegetation." []
synonym: "soil pH amendment" RELATED []
is_a: elmo:3620501 ! chemical application process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations to complement lime application process, which raises pH." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621028
name: seed ball application process
def: "A seeding process in which a human distributes seeds encased in a ball of clay or organic material. Seed balls protect seeds from desiccation and predation and can be dispersed by hand, slingshot, or aerial drop into areas that are difficult to access." []
synonym: "seed pellet application" EXACT []
synonym: "seedbomb application" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620609 ! seeding process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621029
name: hay transfer process
def: "A plant material transfer process in which a human cuts hay from a species-rich donor site and spreads it on a receptor restoration site in order to introduce plant propagules and associated invertebrates." []
synonym: "brush harvesting" RELATED []
synonym: "green hay transfer" EXACT []
synonym: "hay strewing" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620630 ! plant material transfer process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621030
name: sod transfer process
def: "A plant material transfer process in which a human moves intact blocks of vegetation and soil from a donor site to a receptor restoration site in order to introduce plant communities and associated soil biota." []
synonym: "sod transplant process" EXACT []
synonym: "turf transplant process" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620630 ! plant material transfer process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621031
name: forest floor litter transfer process
def: "A plant material transfer process in which a human collects leaf litter and organic material from the forest floor of a donor site and spreads it on a restoration site to introduce seeds, spores, soil invertebrates, and soil microbiota characteristic of forest ecosystems." []
is_a: elmo:3620630 ! plant material transfer process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621032
name: wetland seedbank transfer process
def: "A plant material transfer process in which a human excavates and transports wetland topsoil or sediment, rich in seeds and soil microbiota, from a donor wetland to a degraded or restored wetland receptor site in order to accelerate vegetation establishment." []
synonym: "wetland muck transfer" EXACT []
is_a: elmo:3620630 ! plant material transfer process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621033
name: microbial inoculation process
def: "A biological ecosystem management process in which a human introduces beneficial microorganisms such as nitrogen-fixing bacteria or mycorrhizal fungi spores to soil or plant propagules in order to improve plant establishment and soil function at a restoration site." []
synonym: "bioinoculant application" RELATED []
synonym: "mycorrhizae addition process" BROAD []
synonym: "rhizobial inoculation" RELATED []
synonym: "soil inoculation" RELATED []
is_a: elmo:3620600 ! biological ecosystem management process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations. Mycorrhizae addition process (ELMO:3620645) is retained as a narrower term." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621034
name: municipal legislation process
def: "A legislation process in which a local or municipal government passes bylaws or regulations with pro-conservation goals, such as prohibiting development in sensitive habitats or requiring urban green infrastructure." []
synonym: "local bylaw process" RELATED []
is_a: elmo:3620801 ! legislation process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "5.1.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations to complement provincial/state and national legislation process terms." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621035
name: cut and mulch process
def: "A mechanical vegetation removal process in which a human cuts vegetation and chips or shreds it in place, leaving the resulting mulch on the ground surface. This simultaneously removes standing vegetation and deposits organic matter on the soil." []
synonym: "chop and drop" RELATED []
synonym: "mulch mowing" RELATED []
is_a: elmo:3620021 ! mechanical vegetation removal process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: elmo:3621036
name: mowing process
def: "A mechanical vegetation removal process in which a human uses a mower to cut vegetation to a defined height above ground level. The cut material may be left in place or collected and removed. Mowing is commonly used to manage grassland, meadow, and road verge vegetation." []
synonym: "cutting removal process" BROAD []
is_a: elmo:3620021 ! mechanical vegetation removal process
property_value: ELMOP:hasCASCode "2.3" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Added following Delphi survey recommendations." xsd:string
property_value: skos:broadMatch https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
created_by: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528
creation_date: 2026-03-18T00:00:00Z

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/1
name: Land/water protection
def: "A conservation action in which land or water areas are formally or voluntarily protected from harmful activities to conserve biodiversity." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/ConservationAction ! conservation action
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/1.1
name: Site/area protection
def: "A land/water protection action in which a specific site or area is formally designated for conservation through legal or institutional mechanisms." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/1 ! Land/water protection
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/1.2
name: Resource & habitat protection
def: "A land/water protection action in which specific natural resources or habitats are legally or institutionally safeguarded from exploitation or degradation." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/1 ! Land/water protection
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2
name: Land/water management
def: "A conservation action in which land or water areas are actively managed to maintain or improve their biodiversity values and ecological function." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/ConservationAction ! conservation action
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.1
name: Site/area management
def: "A land/water management action in which a specific site or area is actively managed using on-the-ground interventions to achieve defined conservation objectives." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2 ! Land/water management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.2
name: Invasive/problematic species control
def: "A land/water management action in which invasive or otherwise problematic species are controlled, suppressed, or eradicated to reduce their negative impacts on native biodiversity." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2 ! Land/water management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3
name: Habitat & natural process restoration
def: "A land/water management action in which degraded habitats or disrupted natural ecological processes are actively restored toward a more natural condition." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2 ! Land/water management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3
name: Species management
def: "A conservation action directed at managing, recovering, or maintaining populations of one or more species." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/ConservationAction ! conservation action
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.1
name: Species management
def: "A species management action in which the population size, structure, or dynamics of a species are directly regulated through human intervention." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3 ! Species management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.1.1
name: Harvest management
def: "A species management action in which the harvest or take of a species is regulated or controlled to maintain sustainable population levels." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.1 ! Species management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.1.2
name: Trade management
def: "A species management action in which the trade in a species or its products is regulated or controlled to prevent unsustainable exploitation." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.1 ! Species management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.1.3
name: Limiting population growth
def: "A species management action in which the growth of a species population is actively limited, typically to reduce overabundance or human-wildlife conflict." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.1 ! Species management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.2
name: Species recovery
def: "A species management action in which active interventions are carried out to increase the size or improve the conservation status of a threatened species population." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3 ! Species management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.3
name: Species re-introduction
def: "A species management action in which individuals of a species are deliberately moved to and released at a location where the species has been extirpated or was previously absent." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3 ! Species management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.3.1
name: Reintroduction
def: "A species re-introduction action in which individuals are released into a site within the species' historical native range where the species no longer occurs." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.3 ! Species re-introduction
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.3.2
name: Benign introduction
def: "A species re-introduction action in which individuals are intentionally moved and released at a location outside the species' historical range to fulfil an ecological or conservation function." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.3 ! Species re-introduction
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.4
name: Ex-situ conservation
def: "A species management action in which individuals, reproductive material, or genetic material are maintained outside their natural habitat for the purpose of conserving biodiversity." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3 ! Species management
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.4.1
name: Captive breeding/artificial propagation
def: "An ex-situ conservation action in which animals or plants are bred or propagated under controlled conditions to maintain or supplement wild populations." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.4 ! Ex-situ conservation
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.4.2
name: Genome resource bank
def: "An ex-situ conservation action in which genetic material such as gametes, embryos, or DNA samples are collected and stored for the long-term preservation of biodiversity." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/3.4 ! Ex-situ conservation
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/4
name: Education & awareness
def: "A conservation action in which knowledge, skills, or awareness related to biodiversity and its conservation are communicated to target audiences." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/ConservationAction ! conservation action
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/4.1
name: Formal education
def: "An education and awareness action in which structured, accredited conservation knowledge and skills are delivered through schools, universities, or other formal educational institutions." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/4 ! Education & awareness
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/4.2
name: Training
def: "An education and awareness action in which practical conservation skills or knowledge are provided to specific groups such as practitioners, rangers, or resource managers." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/4 ! Education & awareness
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/4.3
name: Awareness & communications
def: "An education and awareness action in which information about biodiversity threats and conservation solutions is disseminated to the general public or specific audiences through media or outreach." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/4 ! Education & awareness
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5
name: Law & policy
def: "A conservation action in which legal instruments, policies, or regulations are developed, strengthened, or enforced to advance biodiversity conservation." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/ConservationAction ! conservation action
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1
name: Legislation
def: "A law and policy action in which formal laws or statutes are developed, amended, or repealed to provide legal protection or support for biodiversity conservation." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5 ! Law & policy
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1.1
name: International level
def: "A legislation action in which international treaties, conventions, or multilateral agreements are developed or ratified to protect biodiversity at the global scale." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1 ! Legislation
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1.2
name: National level
def: "A legislation action in which national laws or statutes are developed, amended, or repealed to protect biodiversity within a country's jurisdiction." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1 ! Legislation
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1.3
name: Sub-national level
def: "A legislation action in which sub-national laws or regulations such as provincial, state, or municipal statutes are developed or amended to protect biodiversity." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1 ! Legislation
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1.4
name: Scale unspecified
def: "A legislation action in which laws or statutes protecting biodiversity are developed or amended at a jurisdictional scale that is not specified." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.1 ! Legislation
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.2
name: Policies and regulations
def: "A law and policy action in which non-statutory policies, administrative rules, or regulations are developed or strengthened to promote biodiversity conservation." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5 ! Law & policy
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.3
name: Private sector standards & codes
def: "A law and policy action in which voluntary or mandatory standards and codes of practice are developed for the private sector to reduce its negative impacts on biodiversity." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5 ! Law & policy
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.4
name: Compliance and enforcement
def: "A law and policy action in which existing laws, regulations, or standards protecting biodiversity are enforced and adherence is actively monitored." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5 ! Law & policy
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.4.1
name: International level
def: "A compliance and enforcement action carried out through international bodies or mechanisms to ensure adherence to biodiversity-related conventions and multilateral agreements." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.4 ! Compliance and enforcement
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.4.2
name: National level
def: "A compliance and enforcement action carried out by national authorities to ensure adherence to biodiversity-related laws and regulations within a country." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.4 ! Compliance and enforcement
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.4.3
name: Sub-national level
def: "A compliance and enforcement action carried out by sub-national authorities such as provincial or municipal agencies to ensure adherence to biodiversity-related laws." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.4 ! Compliance and enforcement
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.4.4
name: Scale unspecified
def: "A compliance and enforcement action carried out to ensure adherence to biodiversity-related laws or regulations at a jurisdictional scale that is not specified." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/5.4 ! Compliance and enforcement
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6
name: Livelihood, economic & other incentives
def: "A conservation action in which economic, livelihood, or social incentives are used to encourage behaviours or practices that benefit biodiversity conservation." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/ConservationAction ! conservation action
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6.1
name: Linked enterprises & livelihood alternatives
def: "A livelihood and economic incentive action in which alternative income sources or enterprises compatible with conservation goals are developed for local communities." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6 ! Livelihood, economic & other incentives
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6.2
name: Substitution
def: "A livelihood and economic incentive action in which harmful or unsustainable products, practices, or exploited species are replaced with sustainable alternatives to reduce biodiversity impacts." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6 ! Livelihood, economic & other incentives
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6.3
name: Market forces
def: "A livelihood and economic incentive action in which market mechanisms such as eco-certification, sustainable sourcing standards, or consumer demand are harnessed to promote conservation-compatible practices." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6 ! Livelihood, economic & other incentives
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6.4
name: Conservation payments
def: "A livelihood and economic incentive action in which direct financial payments or transfers are made to landowners, communities, or individuals in exchange for managing land in a conservation-compatible manner." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6 ! Livelihood, economic & other incentives
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6.5
name: Non-monetary values
def: "A livelihood and economic incentive action in which the cultural, spiritual, aesthetic, or intrinsic values of biodiversity are recognised and promoted to motivate conservation behaviour." []
is_a: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/6 ! Livelihood, economic & other incentives
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Term]
id: https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/ConservationAction
name: conservation action
def: "A process undertaken by humans or organizations to protect, manage, or restore biodiversity and ecosystem services." []
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: dce:source https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/conservation-actions

[Typedef]
id: BFO:0000050
name: part of
def: "a core relation that holds between a part and its whole" []
subset: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/valid_for_go_annotation_extension
subset: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/valid_for_go_gp2term
subset: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/valid_for_go_ontology
subset: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/valid_for_gocam
property_value: IAO:0000111 "is part of" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "my brain is part of my body (continuant parthood, two material entities)" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "my stomach cavity is part of my stomach (continuant parthood, immaterial entity is part of material entity)" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "this day is part of this year (occurrent parthood)" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Everything is part of itself. Any part of any part of a thing is itself part of that thing. Two distinct things cannot be part of each other." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Occurrents are not subject to change and so parthood between occurrents holds for all the times that the part exists. Many continuants are subject to change, so parthood between continuants will only hold at certain times, but this is difficult to specify in OWL. See http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ro/docs/temporal-semantics/" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Parthood requires the part and the whole to have compatible classes: only an occurrent can be part of an occurrent; only a process can be part of a process; only a continuant can be part of a continuant; only an independent continuant can be part of an independent continuant; only an immaterial entity can be part of an immaterial entity; only a specifically dependent continuant can be part of a specifically dependent continuant; only a generically dependent continuant can be part of a generically dependent continuant. (This list is not exhaustive.)\n\nA continuant cannot be part of an occurrent: use 'participates in'. An occurrent cannot be part of a continuant: use 'has participant'. A material entity cannot be part of an immaterial entity: use 'has location'. A specifically dependent continuant cannot be part of an independent continuant: use 'inheres in'. An independent continuant cannot be part of a specifically dependent continuant: use 'bearer of'." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "part_of" xsd:string
property_value: RO:0001900 RO:0001901
property_value: RO:0040042 BFO:0000002
property_value: RO:0040042 BFO:0000003
property_value: RO:0040042 BFO:0000004
property_value: RO:0040042 BFO:0000017
property_value: RO:0040042 BFO:0000019
property_value: RO:0040042 BFO:0000020
property_value: RO:0040042 BFO:0000031
property_value: seeAlso http://ontologydesignpatterns.org/wiki/Community:Parts_and_Collections
property_value: seeAlso http://ontologydesignpatterns.org/wiki/Submissions:PartOf
property_value: seeAlso "http://www.obofoundry.org/ro/#OBO_REL:part_of" xsd:string
property_value: seeAlso "https://wiki.geneontology.org/Part_of" xsd:anyURI
is_transitive: true
is_a: RO:0002131 ! overlaps
inverse_of: BFO:0000051 ! has part

[Typedef]
id: BFO:0000051
name: has part
def: "a core relation that holds between a whole and its part" []
subset: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/valid_for_go_annotation_extension
subset: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/valid_for_go_ontology
subset: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/valid_for_gocam
property_value: IAO:0000111 "has part" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "my body has part my brain (continuant parthood, two material entities)" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "my stomach has part my stomach cavity (continuant parthood, material entity has part immaterial entity)" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "this year has part this day (occurrent parthood)" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Everything has itself as a part. Any part of any part of a thing is itself part of that thing. Two distinct things cannot have each other as a part." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Occurrents are not subject to change and so parthood between occurrents holds for all the times that the part exists. Many continuants are subject to change, so parthood between continuants will only hold at certain times, but this is difficult to specify in OWL. See http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ro/docs/temporal-semantics/" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Parthood requires the part and the whole to have compatible classes: only an occurrent have an occurrent as part; only a process can have a process as part; only a continuant can have a continuant as part; only an independent continuant can have an independent continuant as part; only a specifically dependent continuant can have a specifically dependent continuant as part; only a generically dependent continuant can have a generically dependent continuant as part. (This list is not exhaustive.)\n\nA continuant cannot have an occurrent as part: use 'participates in'. An occurrent cannot have a continuant as part: use 'has participant'. An immaterial entity cannot have a material entity as part: use 'location of'. An independent continuant cannot have a specifically dependent continuant as part: use 'bearer of'. A specifically dependent continuant cannot have an independent continuant as part: use 'inheres in'." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "has_part" xsd:string
property_value: RO:0001900 RO:0001901
is_transitive: true
is_a: RO:0002131 ! overlaps

[Typedef]
id: BFO:0000062
name: preceded by
def: "x is preceded by y if and only if the time point at which y ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which x starts. Formally: x preceded by y iff ω(y) <= α(x), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point." []
subset: ro-eco
property_value: dcterms:source "http://www.obofoundry.org/ro/#OBO_REL:preceded_by" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000111 "preceded by" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "An example is: translation preceded_by transcription; aging preceded_by development (not however death preceded_by aging). Where derives_from links classes of continuants, preceded_by links classes of processes. Clearly, however, these two relations are not independent of each other. Thus if cells of type C1 derive_from cells of type C, then any cell division involving an instance of C1 in a given lineage is preceded_by cellular processes involving an instance of C.    The assertion P preceded_by P1 tells us something about Ps in general: that is, it tells us something about what happened earlier, given what we know about what happened later. Thus it does not provide information pointing in the opposite direction, concerning instances of P1 in general; that is, that each is such as to be succeeded by some instance of P. Note that an assertion to the effect that P preceded_by P1 is rather weak; it tells us little about the relations between the underlying instances in virtue of which the preceded_by relation obtains. Typically we will be interested in stronger relations, for example in the relation immediately_preceded_by, or in relations which combine preceded_by with a condition to the effect that the corresponding instances of P and P1 share participants, or that their participants are connected by relations of derivation, or (as a first step along the road to a treatment of causality) that the one process in some way affects (for example, initiates or regulates) the other." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "is preceded by" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "preceded_by" xsd:string
domain: BFO:0000003 ! occurrent
range: BFO:0000003 ! occurrent
holds_over_chain: BFO:0000050 BFO:0000062
is_transitive: true
is_a: RO:0002086 ! ends after
inverse_of: BFO:0000063 ! precedes

[Typedef]
id: BFO:0000063
name: precedes
def: "x precedes y if and only if the time point at which x ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: x precedes y iff ω(x) <= α(y), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point." []
subset: ro-eco
property_value: IAO:0000111 "precedes" xsd:string
domain: BFO:0000003 ! occurrent
range: BFO:0000003 ! occurrent
holds_over_chain: BFO:0000050 BFO:0000063
is_transitive: true
is_a: RO:0002222 ! temporally related to

[Typedef]
id: ENVO:01003004
name: derives from part of
def: "A relation between two distinct material entities, the new entity and the old entity, in which the new entity begins to exist through the separation or transformation of a part of the old entity, and the new entity inherits a significant portion of the matter belonging to that part of the old entity." []

[Typedef]
id: RO:0000052
name: characteristic of
def: "a relation between a specifically dependent continuant (the characteristic) and any other entity (the bearer), in which the characteristic depends on the bearer for its existence." []
comment: Note that this relation was previously called "inheres in", but was changed to be called "characteristic of" because BFO2 uses "inheres in" in a more restricted fashion. This relation differs from BFO2:inheres_in in two respects: (1) it does not impose a range constraint, and thus it allows qualities of processes, as well as of information entities, whereas BFO2 restricts inheres_in to only apply to independent continuants (2) it is declared functional, i.e. something can only be a characteristic of one thing.
property_value: IAO:0000111 "inheres in" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "this fragility is a characteristic of this vase" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "this red color is a characteristic of this apple" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "inheres_in" xsd:string
property_value: RO:0001900 RO:0001901
is_functional: true
is_a: RO:0002314 ! characteristic of part of
inverse_of: RO:0000053 ! has characteristic

[Typedef]
id: RO:0000053
name: has characteristic
def: "Inverse of characteristic_of" []
property_value: IAO:0000111 "bearer of" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "this apple is bearer of this red color" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000112 "this vase is bearer of this fragility" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "A bearer can have many dependents, and its dependents can exist for different periods of time, but none of its dependents can exist when the bearer does not exist." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "bearer_of" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "is bearer of" xsd:string
property_value: RO:0001900 RO:0001901
range: BFO:0000020 ! specifically dependent continuant
is_inverse_functional: true

